old attendant, retainer, page, messenger’. Many early bearers of this name were of modest means and cannot have been members of the gentry; in such cases the name may have been used hyperbolically for a low-ranking servant or as a nickname. By the 17th century, the term denoted any member of the landed gentry, but this is unlikely to have influenced the development of the surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Swire","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): variant of   Squire  , from a northern form of the word."]},{"name":"Quire","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Squire  .","Scottish or Irish: shortened form of   McQuire   (see   McGuire  )."]},{"name":"Squires","meanings":["English: variant of   Squire  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Scuderi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carmelo, Salvatore, Angelo, Carlo, Gaetano, Vito, Antonio, Dante, Mario, Rocco, Rosario, Antonino, Biaggio, Eduardo, Ermelinda, Margarita.","Italian (Sicily): status name equivalent to   Squire  , from <i>scudiero</i>, <i>scutiero</i>, dialect <i>scuteri</i> ‘shieldbearer’ (from medieval Latin <i>scutarius</i>, an agent derivative of <i>scutum</i> ‘shield’). In Byzantium, the Greek word <i>skoutarios</i> denoted a member of the imperial guard."]},{"name":"Square","meanings":["English (Devon) and Scottish (Lanarkshire): variant of   Squire  ."]},{"name":"Squier","meanings":["English: variant of   Squire  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Squire was born about 1359, in Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas L Squire. He had at least 1 son with Martha Slader. He died in 1439, at the age of 81."},"et":{"about 1359–1439":"umbes 1359–1439","1359–1439":"1359–1439","–1384":"–1384","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1330–1359":"1330–1359","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","about 1359":"umbes 1359","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","Aft 1384":"pärast 1384","1470":"1470","1439":"1439","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England",",Kent,England.":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1359–1439":"noin 1359–1439","1359–1439":"1359–1439","–1384":"–1384","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1330–1359":"1330–1359","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","about 1359":"noin 1359","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","Aft 1384":"1384 jälkeen","1470":"1470","1439":"1439","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England",",Kent,England.":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1359–1439":"environ 1359–1439","1359–1439":"1359–1439","–1384":"–1384","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1330–1359":"1330–1359","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","about 1359":"environ 1359","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","Aft 1384":"après 1384","1470":"1470","1439":"1439","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, Angleterre","Kent, England":"Kent, Angleterre",",Kent,England.":"Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Thomas Squire est né environ 1359, à Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Thomas L Squire. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Martha Slader. Il est décédé en 1439, à l’âge de 81 ans."},"de":{"about 1359–1439":"um 1359–1439","1359–1439":"1359–1439","–1384":"–1384","1400–1470":"1400–1470","1330–1359":"1330–1359","1359":"1359","1400":"1400","about 1359":"um 1359","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","Aft 1384":"nach 1384","1470":"1470","1439":"1439","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England",",Kent,England.":"Kent, England, United Ki